s|TAG_MOVIE_NEWS|<b>Sushmita Sen To Play Radha In Sholay</b> <br> Date: <A ALT="" TITLE="Bollywood Movie News" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/news/2006/10_23_2006.html">10/23/2006</A> <br> <A ALT="" TITLE="Sushmita Sen" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/actress/sushmita_sen/bollywood_sushmita_sen.html">Sushmita Sen</A> to play the role of widow Radha in Ram Gopal Varma's <A ALT="" TITLE="Sholay Movie Review" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/movie_reviews/2006/sholay.html">Sholay (2006)</A> until now everyone was under the impression that Sushmita would be playing the role of Basanti. She will be replacing the role that was going to be played by <A ALT="" TITLE="Katrina Kaif" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/actress/katrina_kaif/bollywood_katrina_kaif.html">Katrina Kaif</A> . Ram's explains that Radha in the new Sholay will be more practical.<br><hr size="1" width="100%"><b>Katrina Kaif Out of Remake Of Sholay</b> <br> Date: <A ALT="" TITLE="Bollywood Movie News" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/news/2006/10_09_2006.html">10/11/2006</A> <br> <A ALT="" TITLE="Katrina Kaif" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/actress/katrina_kaif/bollywood_katrina_kaif.html">Katrina Kaif</A> has opted out of Ramu's remake of Sholay cites dates problems, but Ramu says otherwise. Verma had announced that Katrina is no longer playing Radha in his Sholay because of her diction. Katrina is currently busy with the following films, Vipul Shah's <A ALT="" TITLE="Namaste London Movie Review" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/movie_reviews/2007/namaste_london.html">Namaste London</A> , Anees Bazmi's <A ALT="" TITLE="Welcome Movie Review" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/movie_reviews/2006/welcome.html">Welcome</A> and David Dhawan's <A ALT="" TITLE="Partner Movie Review" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/movie_reviews/2006/partner.html">Partner</A> .<br><hr size="1" width="100%"><b>Ram Gopal Varma Ki Sholay</b> <br> <font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> Date: <A ALT="" TITLE="Bollywood Movie News" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/news/2006/05_29_2006.html">05/31/2006</A> </font> <br> Ram Gopal Verma has decided to shelve his forthcoming film Time Machine which stared <A ALT="" TITLE="Shahrukh Khan" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/actor/shahrukh_khan/bollywood_shahrukh_khan.html">Shahrukh Khan</A> and instead decided to start work on the remake of <A ALT="" TITLE="Sholay Movie Review" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/movie_reviews/2006/sholay.html">Sholay</A> . It was also announced that <A ALT="" TITLE="Himesh Reshammiya" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/music_director/himesh_reshmiya/bollywood_himesh_reshmiya.html">Himesh Reshammiya</A> , currently the hottest music director turned singer, who will be providing the music for the movie will also be singing the famous Mehbooba Mehbooba for the film. The film stars <A ALT="" TITLE="Amitabh Bachchan" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/actor/amitabh_bachchan/bollywood_amitabh_bachchan.html">Amitabh Bachchan</A> as Gabbar Singh and <A ALT="" TITLE="Urmila Matondkar" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/actress/urmila_matondkar/bollywood_urmila_matondkar.html">Urmila Matondkar</A> will dance to Mehbooba Mehbooba.<br><hr size="1" width="100%"><b>Another film for Amitabh Bachchan</b> <br> Date: 04/05/2006 <br> Ram Gopal Verma announces another project in the mist of still finalizing his current project, <A ALT="" TITLE="Sholay Movie Review" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/movie_reviews/2006/sholay.html">Sholay</A> . RGV announced <A ALT="" TITLE="Nishabd Movie Review" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/movie_reviews/2006/nishabd.html">Nishabd</A> , staring <A ALT="" TITLE="Amitabh Bachchan" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/actor/amitabh_bachchan/bollywood_amitabh_bachchan.html">Amitabh Bachchan</A> and the story is about a 54-year old married man who falls in love with a girl, 36 years younger. The film is scheduled to start production May 1, 2006. The film is based on Vladimir Nakobov’s timeless novel Lolita.<br><hr size="1" width="100%"><b>First it was Saif, and now Abhishek has turned down Veeru's role</b> <br> <font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> Date: 02/02/2006 </font> <br> The role os Veeru in Ram Gopal Verma remake of Sholay was earlier turned down by <A ALT="" TITLE="Saif Ali Khan" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/actor/saif_ali_khan/bollywood_saif_ali_khan.html">Saif Ali Khan</A> and now <A ALT="" TITLE="Abhishek Bachchan" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/actor/abhishek_bachchan/bollywood_abhishek_bachchan.html">Abhishek Bachchan</A> has turned down the role becuase he had given the dates to Maniratnam to act in a English movie. Ramu still has <A ALT="" TITLE="Amitabh Bachchan" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/actor/amitabh_bachchan/bollywood_amitabh_bachchan.html">Amitabh Bachchan</A> signed to play the role of Gabbar Singh.<br><hr size="1" width="100%"><b>Saif Ali Khan declines a Mani Rathnam and Ram Gopal Varma offer</b> <br>Date: 01/19/2006 <br> <A ALT="" TITLE="Saif Ali Khan" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/actor/saif_ali_khan/bollywood_saif_ali_khan.html">Saif Ali Khan</A> declined an offer by Mani Rathnam to work on a bi-lingual film (Hindi and English) and also declined the role of Veeru on Ram Gopal Varma's remake of the hit movie <A ALT="" TITLE="Sholay Movie Review" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/movie_reviews/2006/sholay.html">Sholay</A> . Saif had to choose between three big projects he had been offered and he choose the role of Iago on Vishal Bharadwaj's adaptation of <A ALT="" TITLE="Othello Movie Review" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/movie_reviews/2006/othello.html">Othello</A> .<br><hr size="1" width="100%"><b>Sholay's remake has Katrina playing Jaya role.</b> <br> Remake of 'Sholay' by Ram Gopal Verma has planned to use alman Khan's love interest <A ALT="Katrina Kaif" TITLE="Katrina Kaif" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/actress/katrina_kaif/bollywood_katrina_kaif.html">Katrina Kaif.</A> Highly appealing Katrina who performed a small role in Ramu's 'Sarkaar' would be playing the Jaya Bachchan's role in this remake. Ramu has also signed the 'Rangeela' girl <A ALT="Urmila Matondkar" TITLE="Urmila Matondkar" HREF="http://www.bollywoodmovies.us/actress/urmila_matondkar/bollywood_urmila_matondkar.html">Urmila Matondkar</A> to dance on the remix version of "Mahbooba Mahbboba".<br><hr size="1" width="100%">|g
